      "title": "What is الصفة المشبهة?",
      "titleArabic": "تعريف الصفة المشبهة",
      "content": [
        "الصفة المشبهة (the resembling adjective) is derived from intransitive verbs and indicates a permanent quality or characteristic.",
        "Unlike اسم الفاعل which indicates a temporary action, الصفة المشبهة describes inherent, lasting qualities."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Derived from intransitive (لازم) verbs",
        "Indicates permanent qualities (صفات ثابتة)",
        "Examples: كَرِيمٌ (generous), حَسَنٌ (good), عَطْشَانٌ (thirsty)",
        "Different from اسم الفاعل which is temporary"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "هُوَ رَجُلٌ كَرِيمٌ", "english": "He is a generous man" },
        { "arabic": "الْوَلَدُ حَسَنُ الْخُلُقِ", "english": "The boy is good in character" },
        { "arabic": "هِيَ جَمِيلَةٌ", "english": "She is beautiful" },
        { "arabic": "الْبَابُ ضَيِّقٌ", "english": "The door is narrow" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Common Patterns",
      "titleArabic": "الأوزان الشائعة",
      "content": [
        "الصفة المشبهة has several common patterns: فَعِيل (كَرِيم)، فَعِل (حَسَن)، فَعْلَان (عَطْشَان)، أَفْعَل (أَحْمَر).",
        "Each pattern often has a particular meaning or category of qualities it describes."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "فَعِيل: كَرِيم (generous), عَظِيم (great), جَمِيل (beautiful)",
        "فَعِل: حَسَن (good), بَطَل (hero), حَذِر (cautious)",
        "فَعْلَان: عَطْشَان (thirsty), جَوْعَان (hungry), غَضْبَان (angry)",
        "أَفْعَل: أَحْمَر (red), أَسْوَد (black), أَعْرَج (lame)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "الرَّجُلُ عَظِيمٌ", "english": "The man is great" },
